+## Public site format (match the hosted changelog)
+
+The live site shows each entry roughly as: **date**, **version**, **product**, **tag chips**, **title**, **one-line summary**, then sections **What's New**, **Improvements**, and **Bug Fixes** (use only the sections that apply).
+
+**Bullet style (use everywhere):**
+
+```md
+- **Short label**: Full sentence describing what the user gets or what was fixed, in plain language.
+```
+
+- **Label** = a few words (feature area or theme), Title Case or sentence case — not a PR number or branch name.
+- **Rest** = complete sentence(s), user benefit first.
+
+**Example (Platform, enterprise):**
+
+```md
+## What's New
+
+- **Step-by-step survey flow**: Surveys now guide users through a clearer, sequential experience with progress indicators to reduce drop-off and confusion.
+
+## Improvements
+
+- **Staff directory feedback**: Creating or editing staff now shows clearer validation feedback to help resolve common data issues quickly.
+
+## Bug Fixes
+
+- **Patrol management stability**: Fixed a crash that could occur in patrol management when some details were missing or incomplete.
+```
+
+**Frontmatter** should supply what the site needs for the header row (title, description, date, version, tags). Add **`product`** when your sync maps entries to a product line (e.g. `Platform`, `Platform APIs`, `WhatsApp Agents`) — confirm the exact key with the `wolf-changelog` sync.
+
+```yaml
+---
+title: "Survey Experience & Staff Management Improvements"
+description: "A smoother survey flow and more reliable staff and patrol management"
+date: "2026-01-15"
+tags: ["Enhancement", "Bug Fix", "Enterprise"]
+version: "2.13"
+# product: "Platform"   # if required by your sync
+---
+```
+
+Omit empty sections. For larger releases you may add **Notes**, **Breaking Changes**, or media — keep the same tone: precise, external-facing, no implementation secrets.
