+# Changelog
+
+## Where the public changelog lives
+
+**Investor-facing, hand-written release notes** for the Enterprise Platform are maintained in the **`wolf-changelog`** repository, under:
+
+`changelog/wolf-enterprise-frontend/`
+
+Edit and commit MDX there; that repo builds the hosted changelog site. **Do not** add duplicate `changelog/*.mdx` files back into this app repo.
+
+The **shape** of entries (frontmatter, tags, What’s New / Improvements / Bug Fixes) is still defined in **`.cursor/commands/changelog.md`** — use it when authoring in **wolf-changelog**.
+
+---
+
+## What stays in *this* repo
+
+- **`changelog/internal/from-main/`** — engineering commit digests (not for external audiences). Regenerate with `node changelog/scripts/build-changelog-from-main-by-day.mjs` after `git fetch` (see `changelog/internal/README.md` if present).
+- **`.cursor/commands/changelog.md`** — shared authoring rules.
+
+---
+
+## Not the same as a PR or merge list
+
+| | External changelog | Pull requests & merges |
+|--|-------------------|------------------------|
+| **Audience** | Investors, customers, partners | Engineering |
+| **Where** | **wolf-changelog** `changelog/wolf-enterprise-frontend/` | GitHub / `git log` |
+
+Automated commit dumps are **not** a substitute for the published product changelog.
